sequenceDiagram
  participant Browser
  participant ClientApp
  participant AuthContext
  participant OrdersContext
  participant SocketContext
  participant BackendExpress
  participant SocketServer
  participant Stripe

  Browser->>ClientApp: Load app
  alt Session reestablished (via localStorage and cookie is present)
    ClientApp->>AuthContext: restore user from localStorage
  AuthContext->>SocketContext: connectSocket()
  SocketContext->>SocketServer: socket connect
  SocketServer-->>SocketContext: server_ready
  SocketContext->>SocketServer: request_online_statuses
  SocketServer-->>SocketContext: online_status
  end

  alt User login
    Browser->>ClientApp: submit login form
    ClientApp->>BackendExpress: POST /api/login {email,password}
    BackendExpress-->>ClientApp: {success,user}
    ClientApp->>AuthContext: login(user)
    AuthContext->>SocketContext: connectSocket()
    else Invalid credentials
    BackendExpress-->>ClientApp: {success:false,error:"Invalid credentials"}
  end

  alt User register
    Browser->>ClientApp: submit register form
    ClientApp->>BackendExpress: POST /api/register {fullname,username,email,password}
    BackendExpress-->>ClientApp: {success}
  end


  Note over ClientApp,OrdersContext: Fetch orders on app load if user logged in
  Browser->>ClientApp: Open seller Dashboard page
  ClientApp->>OrdersContext: fetch orders
  OrdersContext->>BackendExpress: GET /api/orders
  BackendExpress-->>OrdersContext: {success,orders}
  OrdersContext->>ClientApp: orders available

  ClientApp->>BackendExpress: GET /api/profile/:username
  BackendExpress-->>ClientApp: public profile

  ClientApp->>BackendExpress: GET /api/gig
  BackendExpress-->>ClientApp: gig list

  Note over ClientApp: Fetch service detail and seller profile when open service detail page
  Browser->>ClientApp: open service detail
  ClientApp->>BackendExpress: GET /api/gig/:gigId
  BackendExpress-->>ClientApp: gig detail
  ClientApp->>BackendExpress: GET /api/profile/:sellerUsername
  BackendExpress-->>ClientApp: seller profile

  Note over ClientApp: Fetch profile data and seller gigs when open profile page
  Browser->>ClientApp: open profile page
  ClientApp->>BackendExpress: GET /api/profile/:username
  BackendExpress-->>ClientApp: profile data
  ClientApp->>BackendExpress: GET /api/gig/seller/:username
  BackendExpress-->>ClientApp: seller gigs

  alt Edit own profile
    ClientApp->>BackendExpress: PATCH /api/profile
    BackendExpress-->>ClientApp: updated profile
    ClientApp->>AuthContext: login(updatedUser)
  end

  alt Upload profile picture
    ClientApp->>BackendExpress: POST /api/upload/profilePicture
    BackendExpress-->>ClientApp: imageUrl
  end

  alt Upload cover banner
    ClientApp->>BackendExpress: POST /api/upload/profileBanner
    BackendExpress-->>ClientApp: imageUrl
  end

  Note over ClientApp: Fetch gig when open checkout page
  Browser->>ClientApp: open checkout page
  ClientApp->>BackendExpress: GET /api/gig/:gigId
  BackendExpress-->>ClientApp: gig detail

  Note over ClientApp: User confirms payment and backend creates Stripe checkout session
  Browser->>ClientApp: confirm pay
  ClientApp->>BackendExpress: POST /api/create-checkout-session {gigId,tier,billing}
  BackendExpress->>Stripe: create checkout session
  Stripe-->>BackendExpress: {sessionUrl}
  BackendExpress-->>ClientApp: {url}
  ClientApp->>Browser: redirect to Stripe checkout
  Stripe-->>Browser: checkout page
  Stripe->>Browser: redirect /success?session_id=...
  Browser->>ClientApp: open success page
  ClientApp->>BackendExpress: GET /api/session/:session_id
  BackendExpress-->>ClientApp: payment details

    Stripe->>BackendExpress: POST /api/webhook-checkout event
    BackendExpress-->>BackendExpress: process webhook event
    alt payment successful
      BackendExpress->>BackendExpress: Create order in database
    end

  Note over ClientApp, SocketContext: Handle incoming chat messages and read events via socket events
  note over SocketContext,SocketServer: Server-side chat socket events
  ClientApp->>SocketContext: emit send_message {orderId,message}
  SocketContext->>SocketServer: send_message
  SocketServer-->>SocketContext: message_received
  SocketContext->>ClientApp: update chat UI / popup / audio
  ClientApp->>SocketContext: emit read_chat {orderId}
  SocketContext->>SocketServer: read_chat
  SocketServer-->>SocketContext: ack